*Who is this for?* 

PLAYNE Education is for students and learners of all levels who are interested in engaging with the art of Shantell Martin to learn about whole-body wellbeing that fosters confidence, critical thinking, emotional resilience, and everyday readiness. Educators, families, and community leaders can use this guide in schools, after-school programs, and beyond.

*How do I use it?* 

The curriculum and resource guide is set up into four key learning sections \- *Anatomy, Wellness & Self Care, Nutrition,* and *Financial Awareness*. Each section can evolve from beginner to advanced content, depending on your classroom level and time available. You are welcome to do all the lessons in order, or choose which lesson is most interesting to you and your classroom. **All that is needed to join the lessons is a pen or pencil, some paper, and yourself**. 

*What is in this guide?* 

The guide has playful activities, projects, conversation starters, and practical resources rooted in art. Each lesson begins with a story about our main character, Shantell, and centers on a piece of her art. **The lessons are designed to be 45-50 minutes long, can be done alone or in groups, and are made to be flexible.** This can also be used as a guide to create dynamic projects, art classes, and programs that support self-discovery through the arts.

*Where can I learn more?* 

Additional resources, related activities, and helpful links are included at the end of each lesson. Learn more about PLAYNE at playne.art

Notes to consider:

* **Time is flexible**: Though each lesson is designed to be about 50 minutes long, each classroom, teacher, and student is different. We have added recommended time-frames for each activity within the lesson, though feel free to modify it to suit your classroom’s needs.   
* **Encourage voices**: Ask open ended questions that do not have yes or no  
* **Build:** Lean into *yes, and*?  
* **Stay Open**: There are no wrong ways to look at and talk about art, our bodies, or our movement in the world; just express what you see and how it makes you feel.   
* **Travel:** The journey *is* the art.
